name: phosphoric acid production, dihydrate process | fluosilicic acid, without water, in 22% solution state | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/28/documentation

The process describes the production of phosphoric acid from phosphate rock with the dyhydrate process in Morocco. As products of the multi output process fertiliser grade phosphoric acid (impure with 51% P2O5) and dilute fluosilic acid (22% in H2O) was considered.

Raw materials, processing chemicals and processing energy, direct emissions to air from process, emissions to air and water from phosphogypsum disposal, emission of radioactive substances from gypsum to air and water, transport of raw materials to the plant, estimation for process infrastructure. The process includes data on emissions from phosphogypsum disposal to the ocean.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2012:Manufacture of fertilizers and nitrogen compounds

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: US, RER, MA.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: RER, US, MA.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription:
This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName.  Weights are based on production volumes.
US: production volume = 2.09e+10 kg/year, weight = 0.8231
RER: production volume = 2.45e+09 kg/year, weight = 0.09649
MA: production volume = 2.04e+09 kg/year, weight = 0.08038
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Production of phosphoric acid assessed mainly with data from one site in Morocco (capacity about 1.3 Mt P2O5 per year). It was was assumed that the data cover about 30-50% of the Moroccan production. The total amount of fluosilic acid produced is not known. The production was assessed with weak data from one source. Therefore no representativity of the data can be given for fluosilic acid production.
